article.description: Kevin Ferguson notched a fourth-consecutive double-double with 20 points and 14 rebounds and Army defeated American University 65-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ferguson's double-double leads Army past American 65-59
article.linkText: Ferguson's double-double leads Army past American 65-59
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Kevin Ferguson notched a fourth-consecutive double-double with 20 points and 14 rebounds and Army defeated American University 65-59 on Saturday. Army missed its first four shots and trailed 7-0 until Ferguson put the Army on the board with a layup that sparked a 12-2 run, helping the Black Knights to pull away to a 24-15 halftime lead. With the win, the Black Knights (15-11, 6-8 Patriot) have four consecutive 15-win seasons for the first time since the 1920-24 seasons. American's 15 points at halftime -- on 6-of-26 shooting (23 percent) -- was the lowest for an Army opponent in any half this season. But American (7-18, 5-9) battled back to within 61-57 on a deep 3 from Delante Jones with 30 seconds left to play. Jones led American with 18 points. Kyle Wilson scored 14 and Tanner Plomb 11 for Army.
